AGI - Israel is buying 40,000 tents to prepare the evacuation of hundreds of thousands of Palestinians from the city of Rafah, in southern Gaza, the Guardian writes. The Israeli prime minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, declared yesterday that it was <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-08/netanyahu-israele-entrance-rafah-guerra-hezbollah-25957889/"> a date was set for the Israeli invasion of Rafah</a>, located on the border with Egypt, without revealing Israel claimed to have a plan to evacuate civilians before its offensive, and the Israeli Defense Ministry published a call for tender Monday to search for a tent supplier. An Israeli official, speaking in anonymity, confirmed that the tents were part of the preparations for Rafah.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<h2> China and Russia's appeal
Chinese Foreign Ministers, Wang Yi, and Russian, Serghei Lavrov, agree on the importance of a ceasefire in Gaza and on the support of the creation of a Palestinian state. During the joint press conference at the end of their meeting in Beijing, Wang said that the recent UN Security Council resolution on the ceasefire in Gaza, on which the United States did not veto, is "winner" and "mandatory". The Chinese Foreign Minister called for "support to the Palestinian nation in the creation of a state" so that "a Jewish nation and an Arab nation can coexist peacefully".
&nbsp;
For its part, Lavrov recalled that Beijing and Moscow defended "the similar provisions" regarding the Gaza conflict within the United Nations Security Council, of which both are permanent members. Lavrov, has been in China since yesterday for an official two-day visit to Wang's invitation and that, according to the Chinese press, could serve as a prelude to President Vladimir Putin's first overseas trip after his recent re-election. The international media hypothesis is a visit to China next month.

